storyInfo: An account of the childhood of  Mephisto and Faust, and their encounter with Talulah.

attributes.content: Eno, what's this book about?
Ah, I read it. So I brought it for you.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: I think you'll like it, Sasha! It's a book about ideals.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Ideals?
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: What are your ideals, Eno?
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: ...Ideals, huh.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: I don't know. Can I have ideals?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Of course you can! Why couldn't you?
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Ah, crap, it's time to go home...
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: You don't want to go?
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: ...I don't want to go home.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: But Eno, you said that if you didn't go home, your father would beat you...
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: But I'll see you tomorrow, right? I can still see you tomorrow.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: I know. I'll put the book and some bread in here.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: ...Sasha, I don't want to go. It's terrible. I'll get beaten even if I go back now.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: So come out tomorrow. If you get hit, you can hit me.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Huh...? Hahaha, Sasha, did you get in another fight? Did they knock your head around?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: You have bruises, so many wounds.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: This way, people know you're hurting. At least someone will know.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Well, I know what you're thinking. But I won't.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: If those kids are still picking on you, let me know! I'll take them all down!
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: I know!
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: See you tomorrow! I'll come and sing to you again!
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: I don't even know what happened to him.
All I know is that he gave me food.
I only know that he could read, and I wanted to read, and he taught me.
I only know that the other kids liked to bully him because he gave me bread and I was stronger, and I hit them and they hit me.
But I don't know what happened to him.
I'm scared. Sasha, I'm really scared.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: I think.... I don't belong in that home. I overheard that my mom.... My mom isn't even in the house.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: The way they look at me, they're all terrifying, and I don't want to go back. I don't want to go back....
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: But there's no food, or anywhere to stay here, it's just.... Just sewers.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: I don't care.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: But....
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Do you hate me too?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: What...? Why?
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Because I like to laugh?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: No.... No. Why would I?
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Because I shouldn't laugh.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Nonsense! Eno, you should keep laughing.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Really?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Really.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Would things be different if he didn't go back that day?
Just because I thought my place was too cold and dirty, I sent him home?
If he hadn't gone back, would it have changed everything?
You're hurt! The wound on your stomach.... What happened, what happened?!
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Sasha.... I've been laughing.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: You see, you told me I could laugh, so I kept laughing.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: I never stopped laughing....
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Sasha, do you still want to hear me sing?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: After that, he visited me from time to time.
And each time he had more and more scars....
So many more.
I realized how much the things I said influenced him. So I started talking less.
Would that make things better?
Your back!
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Your back....
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: ......Does it hurt?
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: This can't keep happening.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Who the hell did this?! Why are they doing this to you?!
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Whoever it is.... they need to be punished! Whatever it is, it needs to be destroyed!
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Eno, take me with you!
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: ...All right.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: I will.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: I didn't know what I'd said.
I didn't know if I could say anything anymore.
What did I do? What the hell did I do?
I've read a lot of books too, but no book ever told me.
Nothing ever told me.
Look. Look at it, Sasha...
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: You told me you wanted to destroy everything that hurt me, didn't you?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Come on.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Your wounds...
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: They're not important. It doesn't matter.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: You see, with one little breath.... It's all better. It's all fine.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Come on, I'll bandage you up! There must be some cloth around here...!
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: That man cut my leg.... Then with one breath, it's better.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: An old man slashed my back. One light touch, and it was fine.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: And it's all thanks to that Originium rock that fat woman shoved down my throat!
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: That's enough, Eno. Really...
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: I can't sing anymore, but you see, it's all from the Originium!
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: There's nothing I can't do!
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Eno!
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: ...You're unhappy. Why? I only did what you told me.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Why are you unhappy?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Obviously they're all happy. Just do what they say and they'll all be happy....
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: ...Because all of your family are assholes. All of them.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Yes!
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: So the kids killed them.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: ...What?
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: The Infected kids who hadn't been driven out of town....
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: What did you do to them?
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: They hit me, too. They hurt you too.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Now, they are like pieces on a chess board. My literal pawns.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: As soon as I healed their wounds, they obeyed my every command.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: I'll take that bunch of ugly, disgusting people, all of them.... All of them!
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: You see, Sasha? You see what I've done?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: We'll burn it down in one magnificent blaze! All of it!
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Sasha, what's wrong with you?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Don't do anything like that ever again.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: But I thought you said....
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: I didn't think it would turn out this way.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Eno, do what you really want to do. Not this.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: I can help you. You don't have to do this.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: But I....
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: That's enough! Just do what you truly want, Eno!
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Not what you're forced to do. Not the bloodshed, not the heartbreak, not the revenge!
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: You don't even like this kind of thing...!
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: ...Sasha...
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: I want to.... Sing....
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Ugh....
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: I couldn't do anything.
I was useless.
Eno....
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: I can't sing anymore.
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: We'll go together. We'll survive.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Survive?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: What's so great about that?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Nothing.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: But we can do it together.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: What are you going to do?
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: This is the Originium I stole from the mine, I was going to sell it for some food.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Sasha!
attributes.name: Eno

attributes.content: Mmm!
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: This way, we're both infected.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Let's survive together.
attributes.name: Sasha

attributes.content: Such things? I'm not interested.
There is no reason for anything you do. There is no meaning to your life on this planet.
No, you don't need anyone to save you...
Pick a name you like.
This one? Good.
Mephisto...
Mephisto. From now on, you are Mephisto. You are no longer what you were.
I don't trust you. I have no right to trust you. The only person you can trust is yourself.
What you did cannot be written off. You will always carry your past, even if you forget, even if you cannot understand what you did.
Everything you do, everything you go through, will become your kindling. They compel you, to keep the fire burning within you....
Until the whole earth is free, until you throw away all that others have given you, until you finally understand yourself.
At that point, you can even discard the name. It's your choice whether you stay or go, live or die.
Mephisto, I can't change your ideals. If you don't have it, go find it. We'll help ourselves.
Who am I? That's not important.
What should you call me?
......Talulah
I'm a rebel, an ordinary woman. I'm nobody. But for now, you can call me Talulah
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: And Talulah didn't say much to me.
She held me tight and rapped three times on my back.
Talulah trusted me. Yelena, Buldrokkas'tee, Lyudmila. They all believed in me.
I thought I could put the childhood I spent in that city behind me.
Only, things changed quickly. It started with what happened in that village.
It was a tragedy. But why did that tragedy make her this way?
Why did things turn out like this?
I'll do whatever you want me to do....
attributes.name: Mephisto

attributes.content: No need. Do as you please.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: I allow it. You are Mephisto, after all.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: But, you said before....
attributes.name: Mephisto

attributes.content: That was years ago.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: It's only natural that some things change over the course of a career.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: If we don't keep up with the times, we're doomed.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: So we, and our fellow Infected, must fight for our collective future.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Anyone can be sacrificed for that ideal.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: I can trust you, can't I?
attributes.name: Mephisto

attributes.content: Yes. Because I am Talulah.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Then I will!
attributes.name: Mephisto

attributes.content: You will, I'm sure you will.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: We can't do it without you. You can do anything, and you can accomplish anything.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Come in.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: You should have seen it all.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Who are you?
attributes.name: Faust

attributes.content: I am Talulah, of course.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: The Talulah I knew... is not you.
attributes.name: Faust

attributes.content: Talulah is just a name. Talulah is just Talulah
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Help him. Mephisto needs your help. Mephisto needs you to give him value. He trusts only you and me.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Talulah would never do that. You're taking advantage of his trust in you!
attributes.name: Faust

attributes.content: None of us have the power to choose.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: You'll do it for him. Everything.
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Or would you rather watch him die?
attributes.name: Talulah

attributes.content: Don't you realize what happened? After passing through that village, Talulah changed completely! She's not the same person!
attributes.name: Faust

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Mephisto

attributes.content: Then why are you doing this?
attributes.name: Faust

attributes.content: I don't trust anyone but you and her.
attributes.name: Mephisto

attributes.content: And I don't want to choose.
attributes.name: Mephisto

attributes.content: Faust, where are we going?
attributes.name: Mephisto

attributes.content: Faust, tell me. What should we do?
attributes.name: Mephisto

attributes.content: ......We survive.
attributes.name: Faust

attributes.content: Isn't it painful to be alive?
attributes.name: Mephisto

attributes.content: It's painful.
attributes.name: Faust

attributes.content: But we can do it together.
attributes.name: Faust

attributes.content: This book, it's a book about ideals.
My ideals are....
